Important Reminder from CVS

I think I might have to push back on that timeline a little bit. I was looking at my schedule and I have a few things overlapping that day. Maybe we can shift the meeting to later in the afternoon or even try for Thursday morning instead. Let me know what works best on your end. I know we wanted to get this wrapped up soon but I also want to make sure we have enough time to actually go through everything properly instead of rushing through it. I feel like if we sit down without distractions we can knock out the main points in about an hour. I have been swamped this week with some personal stuff so I have not had a chance to prepare as much as I wanted to. I will carve out some time tonight to review the notes you sent over and come ready with my thoughts. I appreciate your patience with all of this. I know I have been a bit slower to respond lately. Life has been busy in a good way though. I also wanted to ask if we are still on for that catch-up call next week because I hav!
 e a few things I would love to get your take on. Nothing urgent just some ideas I have been kicking around.

 

CVS

ExtraCare  ·  Member Update

Dear Valued Shopper,

Your ExtraCare® points are ready to use — but not for long.

Your current balance

$463.27

Scheduled to expire TODAY — redeem by TOMORROW or points will be forfeited from 2025.

We wanted to send a gentle reminder so you can put your rewards to good use. ExtraCare points can be applied toward eligible purchases at any CVS store or online at CVS.com—no extra steps needed.

In store

Simply share your ExtraCare card or phone number at checkout. Your available balance will apply automatically.

Online

Sign in to your CVS account and your rewards will be visible at checkout. Apply them before completing your order.

ExtraCare is CVS’s loyalty program where shoppers earn rewards and personalized deals. This reminder helps you use your points on what matters to you.

Redeem My Points Now

Thank you for being a valued ExtraCare member.

We look forward to seeing you soon.

CVS Health  ·  1 CVS Drive  ·  Woonsocket, RI 02895

This is an important service message about your ExtraCare account.

I have been meaning to ask you about that book you mentioned last week. I finally picked up a copy and I am about halfway through it. I have to say I am really enjoying the way the author builds tension in the early chapters. I was not sure about the pacing at first but it really grew on me. I feel like the main character is a bit too stubborn for his own good though. I kind of want to shake him sometimes. Anyway I was wondering if you have read anything else by the same writer or if this was your first one. I am always looking for recommendations. Also thanks again for the tips on the garden. I moved the tomato plants to a sunnier spot and they are already looking happier. I think I was overwatering them so I cut back and now they seem to be bouncing back. I still have no idea what I am doing but it is fun to learn. Let me know if you want to grab coffee this weekend. I am free Saturday morning if that works for you.

